<li><a href="https://arstechnica.com/science/2025/08/study-social-media-probably-cant-be-fixed/">A great interview with Petter T√∂rnberg on his paper about how social media might be structually dysfunctional</a>. &#8220;Rather than bringing us together into one utopian public square and fostering a healthy exchange of ideas, these platforms too often create filter bubbles or echo chambers.&#8221;</li>



